snippet.textDisplay:
It's such a good video, and Anthony really well managed the DissociaDID's little and switches ! Made me so happy ! ❤️
Maybe I got a little uncomfortable when the zooms of the switches occured because I feel like it's such a (i dunno if it's the word, please excuse my french head) intimate (?) moment. Something that could be recorded on caméra, but not zoomed on like on a documentary ? Even if it's kind of a documentary, I feel like a switch is a more vulnerable moment and we shouldn't focus on that but keep a normal view ? (Well if I had DID and had to switch in front of a camera, I would not appreciate it. But they are kind of used to switch on camera now)
Anyway. That was my point of view, and if it's still on the video, it might not bother the DissociaDID system as much as it did for me.
Spreading love to everyone and hope you all have a nice day ! ❤️❤️❤️

snippet.textDisplay: Fix the drama that's been going on. I've commented on Trisha's and Nins channel already. You're an interviewer, coming together with a few YouTubers shouldn't be hard.  PLEAAAAASSEEEE, I suffer from a mental illness as well and I am SO disappointed with you 'advocates' not listening to one another 100%. I hope you all see my comment and hear me out!!! Ahhhhh the drama isn't cool, make something positive from this. Thankyou 😅👏 sorry for the LONG comment. "Anthony, Trisha and Nin all spoke a mix of their opinion, personal experience as well as some facts. A full conversation goes over facts, questions and opinions FULLY. There was no balance on any of their sides. All of their responses are merely replies to one another which all lack positive progression for the conversation. Everyone should chill, apologize for speaking out of ignorance. All three of them spoke too harshly on their own opinion thus, ignorance was shooting EVERYWHERE. Anthony made a video with people who have DID and Nin happened to be on there and as much and Nin may be pleasant, she is ignorant on things as well. She gave a harsh review on Trisha but Trisha is a person who will speak on her opinion regardless of what people think, I respect that but she didn't fully understand what she was talking about in her DID video either. Anthony spoke on Trisha's video trying to be a positive advocate but maybe Trisha didnt intend for 'crazy' to be a bad word in her use. Nobody here spoke one on one so I don't truly care for any of this drama, it's sad. Three grown adults who all struggle in their own way in the spotlight of millions yet not ONE has tried to come together for an open conversation. Sorry for the harsh comments that you've been receiving, Trisha. It is hard to open up on something that's going on in your brain but you don't fully understand. No other YouTuber has even tried to empathize that you could be going through something serious, people just want to debunk you. It's fucked. There are MANY disorders with dissociation, there is quite literally a spectrum for everything. I hope you get the help you need and I will be posting this comment on Anthony and Nins channel. I hope you all come together and make something stronger out of this. I know what it's like to feel crazy, I know what it's like to fully be and act crazy. Subconscious or not, it is not pleasant to feel that way. Everybody is a little fucking crazy anyways, whether you see it or not, humans are insane. I wish you all the best."
